\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The proof uses what's known as 
\series bold
proof by contradiction
\series default
.
 [Does anyone know how proof by contradiction works?] It goes like this:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Assume statement 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is true.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If statement 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is true, then we come to a contradiction of our assumption that 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is true.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Therefore, 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 couldn't have been true to start with.
 Ready?
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
